PIETERMARITZBURG KwaZulu-Natal s provincial budget is set to top R115-billion in the coming financial year a R5bn increase on the current year.This emerged on Thursday when the Finance MEC Belinda Scott presented the provincial budget to the KwaZulu-Natal legislature in Pietermaritzburg.Education and health take the lion s share of the budget with R47,4bn allocated to education and R39,5bn allocated to health a combined 75,5 percent of the total budget in the 2017/18 financial year.About R73bn of the total provincial budget will be spent on wages and salaries.Scott said that R252,3-million had been budgeted for traditional leaders or izinduna as they are known.#Budget2016: Sweeping changes to municipalitiesThis, though, is separate from the R58,9 million that has been allocated to the amaZulu royal household headed up by King Goodwill Zwelithini.The Transport Department is the third biggest recipient of funding, taking up R9,847bn, with most of that to be spent on building roads.Scott said that the provincial government would be following National Treasury guidelines to ensure that procurement is targeted to empower various groups, including African women. We are not talking this over. We are walking the talk, she said.African News Agency